    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>The equation {@g@} represents an ellipse. Find its centre, the semi-major and semi-minor axes, and the coordinate positions of the foci.</p>

<p>The centre is \((\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]],[[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]\()\) [[feedback:prt1]]</p>

<p>The semi-major axis is the [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] and the semi-minor axis is [[input:ans4]][[validation:ans4]] [[feedback:prt2]]</p>

<p>The foci are at coordinate position \((\) [[input:ans5]] [[validation:ans5]], [[input:ans6]] [[validation:ans6]]\()\) and  \((\) [[input:ans7]] [[validation:ans7]], [[input:ans8]] [[validation:ans8]]\()\)</p>
[[feedback:prt3]]]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>By completing the square we may rewrite {@g=0@} in standard form as:</p>
\[{@f+1=1@}\]

<p>Hence, the centre is at \(({@c[1]@},{@c[2]@})\), \(a={@a@}\), and \(b = {@b@}\). Since {@if is(a>b)= true then "\\(a \gt b\\)" else "\\(a\\lt b\\)"@}, the major-axis is {@if is(a>b)= true then "\\(x\\) axis" else "\\(y\\) axis"@} and the minor-axis is {@if is(a>b)= true then "\\(y\\) axis" else "\\(x\\) axis"@}.</p>

Finally, for the foci, we calculate the eccentricity as \(e = {@ec@}\). Then we note that the foci will be {@if is(a>b)= true then "\\(\\pm ae\\)" else "\\(\\pm be\\)"@} from the centre of the ellipse \(({@c[1]@},{@c[2]@})\). Hence the foci are at \(({@foci[1][1]@},{@foci[1][2]@})\) and \(({@foci[2][1]@},{@foci[2][2]@})\).]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
